results.description:
My Story: I grew up in Pennsylvania 2 hours outside of Philly near Lebanon. Needless to say I have been a diehard Eagles fan for as long as I remember. Shortly after collage life’s journey lead me to Seattle WA where I started an Eagles Meet-up. On average we drew 50-60 Eagle fans every Sunday. I moved to Connecticut 3 months ago & hope to start a similar group in the Stamford, Norwalk, Fairfield & Westchester County area. There’s nothing like watching Eagles football surrounded by fans who “get it”! 

The Plan: By far the biggest challenge in starting a group like this is finding a suitable location. Fortunately Castle Bar & Grill (on Summer St) has agreed to give us access to their private room. 
The following are benefits Eagle fans can expect during every game. 

• Sound: No more listening to the Giants/Jets in a crowded bar! 

• Drink specials 

• Food specials 

• A community of diehard Eagle fans!

Important Note 

In order to secure the room we NEED a minimum of 10 people to attend each week. This is simply to make it cost effective for Castle to keep the room open for us. We’ll use the first few weeks as a test to gauge interest level & attendance. Please RSVP so we can get an accurate head count.
results.name: Philadelphia Eagles Fans of Stamford CT

topics.name: Ending the Isolation of Chronic Illness

results.description:
There are no scoliosis meetups or support groups in the NYC area to my knowledge. I have moderate scoliosis, and I decided to start one. If alcoholics have AA and drug addicts have NA, and there are support groups for a slew of other types of mental health and health issues, it's about time scoliosis got a support group of its own. We suffer too, don't we? Doesn't our condition impact our lives in significant ways, mentally and physically?

The only place where I read about the spiritual-psychological aspect of scoliosis was in a text written by Katharina Schroth, who founded the Schroth Method of scoliosis treatment in the early 20th Century (http://www.scoliosisjournal.com/content/6/1/17):

"Curvature of the spine, or scoliosis, is a precarious formal defect in terms of health, appearance, and the spiritual-psychological aspect. When attempting to help a scoliotic with this defect, we must not view the matter primarily from the mechanical standpoint, namely the malfunctioning body. For we have before us not a mechanical structure of bony levers and the muscles that move them, but rather an unfortunate person who has lost the form originally created for her and who cannot restore it by herself. With all scoliotic people, the cause probably lies partly in the mental realm. Envision what the expression "not in good form" means. Imagine the mental state of a child scolded by his mother. The psychic depression and loss of equilibrium are immediately visible in his abnormal bodily form. How wonderful the form of a little child's body is! What a victorious, natural, matter-of-fact nature he has in the representation of his Self, and in every movement and in all of his life statements.

However, let us observe a school class three or four years later. What has happened to these children? Almost all are missing their original sense of complete, untroubled comfort within. Many children have pronounced signs of suffering in their faces, and their depressed mental state finds expression in their bodies.

Why do gymnastic attempts to erect such a troubled child often fail completely? It is because they approach the child much too mechanically, much too much in the form of exercises, without first becoming familiar with his life difficulties, his unfulfilled needs, which to the adult may seem trivial. Straightening of the external person will only succeed when we can erect the inner person, open an avenue of hope, and allow him to breathe a sigh of relief." (Lehnert-Schroth, Christa, P.T. Three-Dimensional Treatment for Scoliosis, page 5)

Also, I must credit this video for inspiring me to move forward with this group: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yGLzpt3caHw

Physical therapists can't help us deal with the mental issues that are getting in the way of our exercises, which in many cases renders the exercises useless. I believe a support group made up of other people with scoliosis is a crucial way of trying to address the psycho-spiritual contributors of this condition.
results.name: Scoliosis Support Group

results.description:
The NY Sharing Economy Meetup connects the different groups and people in New York City interested in the sharing economy. It is intended for tech and non-tech alike, public and private, academics, founders, students, investors, city officials, visitors to NYC and more. We post sharing economy happenings across New York. 

The Sharing Economy often involves a shift towards interactions between peers and a more sustainable use of resources. It creates a new economic paradigm built on distributed networks of connected individuals and communities rather than on centralized institutions. (You may have heard people refer to it as collaborative consumption, the peer economy and the collaborative economy.) This new economic model is changing our daily lives, our communities, what it means to have a “job,” our cities, and the planet. 

The NY Sharing Economy Meetup is a collaborative organization driven by its members. All members are invited to suggest events that will enable the community to better understand the potential and challenges of this new economy, leverage new technologies, benefit from new opportunities, hear about cutting-edge research, experience new ways of sharing and much more. Examples of groups involved include Let's Collaborate!, New York University, OuiShare, Peers and more.

Note: events that are organized by external parties will be notified as 'PARTNER events'
results.name: NY Sharing Economy Meetup

We will learn the self defense system taught in Taekwondo, along with Krav Maga, military combatives, and any other style that you may have trained in. All skill levels are welcome to join, we will all learn from each other in a fun and friendly environment. For those with little to no experience, we will start with the basics and increase complexity was we move along. For those with experience, be ready to get a good workout while furthering your arsenal of skills. We will meet on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays from 7:30pm to 8:30pm. 

The head instructor will be Vinicius Raposa, who has over a decade of experience in various martial arts. Sir Raposa is an Internationally ranked Black Belt in Taekwondo, with unique self-defense experience developed from his time training with the Brazilian Marines at the Escola Naval, Rio de Janeiro and being the highest ranked Kombato practitioner in the United States. You will be in good hands.

-Dates: Every Monday, Wednesday and Friday

-Times: 7:30pm - 8:30pm

-First meeting is FREE

862-305-0369 (call/text)

Our objective is to present public concerts of Songs from India - different regions and languages, in a chorus style, sprinkled with solos. We generally stay away from Bollywood songs. In concerts, we employ live orchestra for accompaniment. Our orchestra is a collection of Indian and Western instruments. While our music is authentically Indian, our performance is a bit fusion in style. Our presentation style is formal and professional, sort of like that of the New York Philharmonic in Lincoln Center.

Our recent concert on October 4, 2015, consisted of 12 non-Bollywood songs from different regions of India. It was a spectacular success and received 10+ minutes spontaneous standing ovation.

We are always looking for new singers to join us. If you would like to sing with us or play ANY Indian instrument reasonably well, please contact us. We are located in Hastings on Hudson, NY.

results.description:
My name is Camille, and I am the best selling author of "How to Lose Water Weight", "Bye Bye Thunder Thighs", and "The Thigh Gap Hack". I love all things fitness related and this group is a manifestation of one of my all time favorite interests - experimenting with new exercises and workouts! (Please click on any of the links to check out my books)


ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events - NYC meet up group, you'll get first wind of the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, classes / workshops all happening in this great city of ours for absolutely zero dollars (and from time to time very steep discounts)!


 Sure you could comb the web for *some of these events and attend all by your lonesome, but going to these workout classes and beauty events stag, while common, kind of sucks. How can you enjoy your free cocktails, hors d'oeuvres and tunes or share your sense of accomplishment at completing a butt kicking working, if you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

Having been to many of these fitness and beauty events I see participants who share so much in common barely connecting with each other because the social aspect isn't fostered or organized - (not that they're to blame.. it's enough work throwing together and hosting these things!)


That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! 

Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get to discover and experience dance/fitness classes and be exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!


PLEASE NOTE: 

While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!), we will also be sharing events that are open to the public and require RSVP's to get in. 

I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.
results.name: Free Fitness & Beauty Events

results.description:
The NYC Career Design Meetup has officially turned 1 year old! The last 13 months have brought together over 700 people to discuss how to build a killer career in this fun, furious city. 

This meetup is active—we do a lot of exercises. Most of them are engineered to help you (and your colleagues or teammates) build skills in the following three ares:

1) Purpose. What do you find rewarding? What job should you do? What product should you make? What do you need to change, add, or delete from your professional toolkit to pursue what's rewarding—and still make money?

2) Pitching. Once you know what you want to do, how do you formulate a plan for doing it? How can you communicate that plan to other stakeholders in a way that makes them see your vision? 

3) Publicity. What's the message you take to the wider world? Whether you're job hunting, fundraising, or Kickstarting, narratives matter: what will yours be? 

I'm a former senior editor at Fast Company and management consultant who has coached Fortune 100 executives on agile work, product ownership, and ways of working. Today I'm editor of Supertemp.com and a venture investor in early-stage startups.
results.name: Career Design Exercises

results.description:
Calling everyone interested in standing up against hate, strengthening ties of communication and cooperation between Muslims and Jews in New York City! 

The New York City Muslim Jewish Solidarity Committee (NYMJSC) was originally initiated by the Foundation for Ethnic Understanding. The committee is a grassroots group of Muslim and Jewish activists, leaders and community members committed to working together. 

The NYC Muslim-Jewish Solidarity Committee is locally organized and has three focus areas:

- Standing Up for Each Other: Muslims and Jews taking joint public stands against hate crimes, incitement or discrimination directed at either community
- Learning About Each Other: Counteract Islamophobia and anti-Semitism within our respective communities
- Organizing and Publicizing: cultural, festive and social service events in order to deepen communal ties and allow individual Jews and Muslims to connect on a personal level

The committee will meet monthly to plan for different types of events and more frequently when crises between the two communities in NYC arise.

Please check out our Facebook group here: https://www.facebook.com/pages/NYC-Muslim-Jewish-Solidarity-Committee/816752598371675?fref=ts
results.name: NYC Muslim-Jewish Meetup

Do you enjoy reading the Tarot? Are you studying the Tarot? This group is for people who are seeking to increase their tarot skills for their self-development and for divination. We will explore ways to develop our intuitive reading skills through the use of decks and spreads. We will share the many ways we each use tarot. The emphasis is on exploring, exposing and expanding knowledge via experiential learning with spreads rather than direct teaching. The goal is to form a group of  about 6-8 core members who meet on Friday nights from about 7pm until about 9pm at least once or twice every month. It would be great to work from shared texts such as The Absolute Beginner's Guide to Tarot,   Power Tarot or the Tarot Bible or Tarot for Yourself.

Ideas for future meetups include:

•  Practicing card spreads from one card up to twelve cards.

• Using comparative tarot spreads to deepen understanding of each card.

• Speed reading sessions during which members perform brief private readings for one another

• Exercises from books such as 365 Tarot Activities by Deanna Anderson or The Tarot Activity Book by Andy Matzner, or Tarot for Every Day by Cait Johnson.

results.description:
Firstly, if you are a writer and would like to have pages read, please contact me so I can book you – my ballpark is 4 writers per meetup - there are limited spaces as this is my personal home.

The evening will go something like this:

Approximately four writers will bring 10 or so pages of original writing, generally feature or short scripts. Please bring enough hard copies of your material for each part you need to cast – and don’t forget to cast the narrator – this is often the most important part! Please highlight the lines for each given character- it will make it much easier for the actors.

During the first 15 minutes or so the writers will cast the parts to any actors (or non-shy writers) who are attending. Writers, feel free to give the actors any general notes, caveats, special pronunciations, contexts, etc, but try not to go full Kubrick, as this is a cold reading!

Then we’ll do the reading (the fun, without-a-net part) and then we’ll give a few minutes of feedback. Important: the level of feedback will be directed by the writer. In other words, the writer is invited to ask for general feedback (“Hey, what do you think?”), specific feedback (‘Do we believe Julie when she tells Sam that she wants to keep the baby, regardless of the consequences???”), or no feedback at all (which is perfectly acceptable – just hearing it in the room and seeing if people are laughing and crying in the right places is often enough.)

Bathroom/refreshment break halfway through, then we’ll rock it out till ten or so.

I’ll have some provisions on hand, but please feel free to bring a bottle of wine/pellegrino/pringles/artisanal cheese/your grandmother’s fresh baked cookies, etc…
results.name: Union Square Writer/Actor Group

Psychology Dinners is another social innovation experiment created by Glen Brauer inspired from the ongoing success of Philosophy Dinners (PhilosophyDinners.org). Click here to view some feedback from previous Philosophy Dinners events held in cities around the world.

This group is for people who value fun and engaging discussions with intelligent, open-minded and friendly people. This Meetup group was created as part of a non-profit global initiative using practical psychology to bring together strangers and build community.


When will the first event take place?

This depends on how long it takes for members to join this Meetup group.  Typically a Meetup group requires at least 30 members in order to get a turnout of at least 6 people.


What will be the topic for the first event?

I will be sending out a poll to decide that once enough members join this group.


The format for these events will be very similar to Philosophy Dinners:

- open-minded individuals who are as intelligent as they are friendly

- 1 thought-provoking topic provided in advance so you have time to ponder it

- Food for Thought videos provided in advance of event 

- events are held in a charming restaurant

- restaurant is close to public transportation

- 6 people at each table (so everyone has a chance to speak)

- 1 discussion facilitator at each table (members take turns being facilitators)

- thought-provoking questions (discussion notes) are provided by Glen Brauer to the facilitators in order to stimulate the discussions.


There are no membership fees but a small fee is required when signing up for events which goes towards Meetup costs, the time required to research and produce the discussions notes, booking restaurant reservations, scheduling the events, and coordinating the facilitators.

If this sounds interesting to you then click "Join Us" on the top-right of this screen then RSVP to events when they are posted. Members receive email notifications when new events are scheduled.


The Psychology Dinners Facebook Group

The purpose of the Psychology Dinners Facebook group is to cultivate the global citizen mindset; by enriching our perspectives through the sharing of insights before and after the events take place in our individual cities.

Click here to join the Psychology Dinners Facebook Group


For more information please visit our home page:

http://www.psychologydinners.org

results.description:
We believe that programming languages, like spoken languages, require a close-knit user community in order to thrive. Scala Stammtisch is founded to bring people together who want to learn, share, and improve functional programming in Scala.

According to Wikipedia, “A Stammtisch is an informal group meeting held on a regular basis, and also the usually large, often round table around which the group meets. A Stammtisch is not a structured meeting, but rather a friendly get-together.”

We are the Scala Stammtisch of NYC, and we invite you to the table.

Format

While most technical meetups optimize for one-to-many communication, Scala Stammtisch aims for 15-to-15 discussion of technical topics.

We discuss one topic in a month’s worth of weekly meetups. Three discussions of the same material repeat on a fixed schedule each week; members should plan to attend only one of these. A fourth gathering takes place in an even less structured, and potentially raucous, setting.

The first 3 meetups for a topic will have an RSVP limit of 15. We will take attendance and no-shows will not be tolerated in the group, though members may change their RSVP with impunity from the time of the announcement up until 12pm of the day of the meetup.
results.name: Scala Stammtisch

results.description:
"Conversations around timeless articles from weeklies and dailies and search for intelligent life among neighbors" is for people who read serious journalism in search for “the best, which has been thought and said”, and want to discuss their finds with likeminded readers.

This is an article discussion meetup for people whose main interest are books. Why article rather than book discussion group then? A book discussion group is not for people who take books seriously, i.e. “have a sense of purpose for reading” (Daniel Bell). They cannot take a detour from the reading path defined by their own questions and interests even for sake of finding people they speak the same language with. An article discussion group allows finding people of the same quality as a book group while making much lesser demand on your reading time.

A serious magazine or newspaper seems to be the only place where you can find intelligent life in public space. Good periodicals might be the only link between people who think. This is the reason for creating the meetup.

This group is for readers who from time to time come across a fascinating article and want to discuss it with others both for better understanding of things and for pleasure of being with people who share your interests.

I am talking about an occasional outstanding article with eye-opening analysis or a review of a great book (just published or classic), not about daily reporting.

For sake of describing this group I’d like to restate the obvious - a few of many things that one may get from a good newspaper if he goes past news:
1. Understanding political world we live in - insightful analysis of major issues of politics – both domestic and foreign;
2. Opportunity to hear people with greater wisdom and knowledge than your own (in our interactions in person we are usually limited to people of our own level);
3. Invaluable tips for continuing study of Humanities on your own;
4. Knowledge for dealing with earthly problems of our lives.

It is easy to miss and never discover articles and tips about books that would be of most interest to you or even “change your life” because there are too many worthy newspapers and magazines for one person to keep up with. It is another reason for this meetup.

Articles will not be limited to current ones. Selection criteria are topic and quality - publication date does not matter – we will be discussing pieces that are “timeless”.
A sample list of articles that follows this description will give you an idea of what kind of things we may discuss. People with a different range of interests who like the idea of this group may want to create meetups that reflect their interests.

Technically this group is limited to discussion of articles, but in reality it should allow discussing any topic that may interest you because over years your favorite newspapers and magazines most likely have had an article on anything you can ever think of.

Periodicals do have online forums, but they are a poor ersatz for a conversation in person and a poor tool for selecting people to talk to (before joining this meetup you will be offered a few questions to determine if the group matches your interests). Unfortunately there are no gathering places for those who want to meet people to discuss works of journalism. This group is designed to serve a role of such place.

Basics on how the group will operate
1. The leader will select an article (or a few) for a discussion using recommendations of the group and his own findings and post the selection approximately two weeks before a meeting. In addition to discussing articles we may want to share tips about articles and books that we find interesting.
2. We will restrict freedom of speech by a 2-3 min. limit per person per comment except instances when the group wants to hear more. Taking numbers might be another good idea.
3. Initial plan is to meet once a month – most likely we will be meeting on Mondays.
4. Meetings will be held in Manhattan.

Sample articles
List of abbreviations:
NYT - New Your Times

The purpose of this group is share resources and practices so that we can nurture ourselves so that we have the joy and strength we need to live courageously, and so nurture others and the earth.  The group is led by LoraKim Joyner, wildlife veterinarian and minister (that's me).  My goal is to grow our numbers and commitment so that we can derive pleasure and joy from this beautiful earth, and so care for what we may, while we can. Other people and species need us to be as whole and as powerful as we can. The Conservationist Way is one pathway for this deep living and giving.  When we meet, I will facilitate specific practices and discussions to nurture ourselves so that we can nourish all of nature.

Please join if you wish to live more strongly connected to life around you, and if you wish to do something for others, such as addressing climate change, loss of biodiversity, extinction, or poverty.  If you arent' sure what you can do with limits on your energy, time and resources, do not hestiate and come join us. There are so many ways to preserve beauty on this earth, even in your daily routine.  

Everyone is welcome, because the earth needs us to be conservationists.

What is a conservationist?  It is you, or can be, for.....

A conservationist is one who increases knowledge and awareness of nature, and uses that understanding to save themselves and the world.

To find out more, go here.

Let us join one another so that our experiences and compassion can guide the way on the path of conservation and joy.

results.description:
The PMP Exam Prep Network Meetup: 5 Boroughs/NYC Area  is for people preparing for the Project Management Institute's (PMI) Project Management Professional (PMP) application and certification test

This MeetUp is to collaborate in studying and sharing resources with other PMP exam preppers.

The MeetUp group is designed to: 

Arrange in-person study sessions (parallel study, collaborative study, etc.) 

• Parallel study: 2 or more PMP Exam Preppers meeting to study same place/time, but not necessarily collaborating (side by side study)

• Collaborative study: 2 or more PMP Exam Preppers meeting to study together 

Share PMP:

• Application preparation resources

• Study plans

• Study aids 

• Other PMP application/exam preparation support resources

Connect to any ongoing PMI and/ PMI NYC study groups/events/resources

ONGOING MEETINGS

Members can arrange meetings and announce them here on the MeetUp.  Confirm the MeetUp time and location in the days leading up to it and the day of.  This way we can grow the network and number of study session options throughout the boroughs/NYC area.

Study sessions/MeetUps should be held in public places with free wifi with excellent, reliable internet connectivity.  The best places will have the table space to accommodate members and studying and sitting for an extended period.  Libraries, community-based coworking/meeting spaces; establishments with a la carte beverage/foods with no waiter/table service and no tipping preferred (Starbucks/cafes, etc).  

Meetings: We plan to hold at least one in-person meeting per week and encourage members to host in-person study sessions at locations/times convenient to them, if they would like more options.  

Connect & Share: We will use platforms such as email, list serve, file sharing and group SMS messaging to facilitate resource sharing and setting up study sessions.

If you would like to join the PMP Exam Prep NYC area Network, send a message with:

• a description of where you are in the PMP application and exam preparation process

• your planned timeline for submitting the application and taking the PMP exam

• where you would like to have PMP study session

• resources you can share that can be of help to others in this Network.
results.name: PMP Exam Prep Network Meetup: 5 Boroughs/NYC Area

results.description:
Do you like to dance? Are you interested in Scottish or Celtic music and culture? Would you like to meet great people, get some exercise, and have fun? Then come dance with us! Beginners are welcome; you don't need to bring a partner; you don't need any special costume, just soft-soled shoes with no heels and clean soles (to keep the dance floor clean -- you can change into them when you arrive).

Scottish country dancing is a social dance form where you dance with a partner in a set of couples, somewhat like square dancing or contra dancing. In each dance you will do a set of patterns using skipping steps, which are taught and practiced during the weekly classes. There are several dance parties throughout the year, as well as more formal balls in which dancers from all across the region come together and dance to live music. Each session has a break for tea and snacks during which you can rest and socialize. The dancers are very friendly and will always help you out if you get confused or forget what to do next.

Here's an example of what it looks like (and another).

results.description:
Asian Society and Culture in Westchester, New York

This group is for Aisans, people interested in Asian culture professionally and those interested in Asian languages.


The age of this groups members is 20-40.

The group meets in Westchester, New York and occassionally in Manhattanb, New York.  We are going to have events in all major Westchester cities.  This includes;  White Plains, Yonkers, and Tarrytown.

Asian Society and Culture in Westchester, New York has activities for singles and families.  If an activity is for families it says (FAMILY ACTIVITY) on posting.

This is a meetup group for people in Westchester County, New York that are interested in Asian Culture and activities that are typically Asian.  Asian Culture of Westchester, New York is a New York group about Asian community and studies.  We engage in monthly activities, the majority of which are in White Plains, New York.  We do have activities planned at other Westchester, New York locations.    At least 3 times a year we are going to have an activity in Manhattan, New York.  The activities of the group are either based on Asian culture or are social events exclusively for people interested in Asian culture.  

You need to apply for membership into this group. This is to keep out unwanted people.  We do not want people joining this group simply to meet foreign women, or who are not deeply into Asian culture, but seek meager entertainment.  This group is for people who are members of the Asian community.  You do not have to be Asian to join this group.  This is a group for people who are seriously interested in Asian culture and Asians!  We do no permit people who are voyeurs or who do not take the groups subject matter seriously.  Please do not let this discourage you.  This is a security measure to allow us to have a high quality and more productive group.


The activities of this group include:

Asian Bar Nights

Asian Nightclub Nights

Asian Social Networking Events

Asian History Discussions

Asian Religious Discussions

Chinese New Year Celebrations

The Spring Blossom Festival

Kabuki Theatre

Karaoke

Asian Movie Viewing Nights

Visiting Koreatown.

Visiting Flushings Chinatown

Visiting Manhattan's Chinatown and Canal Street.

Visiting Manhattan, New York fir Asian culture events.

Visiting Buddhist Temples and Shrines

Lectures on Asian Culture

Asian Language Exchanges

The group meets every month.

Tet Celebration

The group is lead by a native New Yorker, who is a Buddhist/Taoist instructor and martial arts teacher.  The organizer is also an active member of the Asian community in; New York and Hawaii.  The organizer enjoys; Asian clubs in New York, karaoke, surfing, and the arts.


Thank you,

Erik

The Asian Culture in Westchester New York Meetup Organizer

results.description:
(best viewed in desktop version).

A sketch group for nudist male artists where artists take turns posing for each other. Our focus is to draw the male figure and depict masculinity in an open-minded, sex-positive nature not found in traditional drawing groups. When both the model and the artist are naked, they are on equal footing, encouraging openness and camaraderie. Sex or touching is not allowed except as part of a pose; some of which are homoerotic; please read the rules and FAQ below. 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CRITERIA TO JOIN THIS GROUP:

• individuals who present themselves with primarily masculine or male features, including transgendered men

• visual artist (mandatory, any level from beginner to experienced), all non-smelly mediums except photography. Since we pose for each other, we don't accept guys who only want to pose. 

• comfortable being nude with fellow artists, willing to pose naked for other artists

• friendly, respectful

• photo in profile (headshot/face preferred)

• be local or have plans to travel to NYC

First-time artists must sign a form allowing (or not allowing) us to photograph their artwork done during the session and publish on the group’s sites and social media. We generally post artwork only without any identification. It's okay to decline but still fill out a form. If you decline, don’t put your drawings out for the photographer.

(Scroll down for additional info)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

STANDARD RULES:

The rules are the same whether in a studio or a private home. Any variations will be announced. This is a drawing group that explores sex-positive poses of the male figure, often including homoerotic poses.

No photography of people without permission.

No sexual activity anywhere in the building, other than as part of a pose.

When you’re not posing, erections are natural and okay but stroking is not.

RULES ABOUT POSES

If you don’t want touching of any kind, tell your partner or do a solo pose.

Plan your pose before getting on the model stand.

We love erotic/sexual poses but they are totally optional. If you do a sexual pose, talk it through with your partner. Poses are not an excuse to have sex with an unwilling partner. Don’t assume. It’s always okay to say no or stop. If you don’t have CLEAR consent, don’t get sexual.

A little movement is okay, but come back to the same position and hold it. 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PRIORITY RSVP AND "NO-SHOW" POLICY:

To reward regular attendance and reduce “no-shows”, we have a priority RSVP system similar to airline priority seating. To attend a session, everyone must first join the waitlist. RSVPs will be confirmed by group (Goldstar, Fan, NewlyJoined all). http://www.meetup.com/Mens-Naked-Drawing-Group-NY/pages/Priority_RSVP_and_no-show_policy

VOLUNTEER ROLES (this is a group effort):

• Bring healthy snacks/refreshments to share (optional).

• Photographing artwork

• Music (bring your device, i.e. iPod, etc.)

• Thinking of interesting poses – all artists

• Setting up and cleaning up

ADDITIONAL INFO:

We meet 3-4 times per month, usually Tuesdays and Sundays. Please check the schedule.

Multiple locations. Address given to members only.

RSVP via Meetup only.

Fee: $15 cash. Credit cards accepted for advance payment. Use the link in the event description. Special sessions may have a higher fee.

Arrive 15-30 minutes before event start time. Everyone sets up. 

Overall session time is 3 hours. It’s a 2-1/2 hour drawing session with a little social time before and breaks during.  Everyone cleans up after.

Bring all your own materials, drawing boards, portable easels, etc. Most guys draw on pads on their laps. There is a sink available for rinsing your brushes.

Bring a towel or sit on your shirt. Please be hygienic.

Be mindful of your stuff (wallet, phone, etc). MNDGNY or the venues are not responsible for lost or stolen items.

Full nudity of all participants is required for the duration of the session. Tuesday venue: footwear is recommended when not on the model stand.

Each artist should think about his possible poses in advance while the other artists should offer friendly suggestions. 

Please put out some of your drawings so others can see them. If you’re working in a notebook, show your drawings to the person taking photographs so he can take some snapshots. Take your drawings home with you!

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS:

I DON'T KNOW HOW TO DRAW; IS THERE ANY INSTRUCTION? There is no instruction, but beginner artists are welcome to try us out as long as you have the interest and make the effort to draw. From time to time, there will be special classes with instruction from a naked teacher; please check the schedule.

I'VE NEVER BEEN TO A NAKED EVENT BEFORE. WHAT'S IT LIKE? We're a friendly bunch and nonjudgmental. We have a wide range of ages and body types. At studio venues, there are usually about 15-20 artists, at private homes about 10 artists. Everyone gets fully undressed after checking in and stays naked for the entire session. It's quite natural and relaxed. However, unlike a typical, strictly non-sexual naturist activity, the poses can be sexual.

I'VE NEVER POSED BEFORE. Many of our members had never posed before joining our group. We'll help you out if you want, so no need to stress out about it. It might be easier to pose together with someone else to start. There is a sign-up sheet for poses with about 12-15 posing slots per session (varying lengths 5-20 minutes) so not everyone poses at each session. Poses are up to each artist posing. They can be classical, athletic, dance-like, sexy, etc. Erotic poses are welcome but not required. 

IS THIS A GAY GROUP? Many of our members are gay, but we are open to men regardless of sexual orientation. In fact, we don't talk about it much. However, some artists create poses that are homoerotic/sexual so you should be comfortable with that.

WHAT'S THE SEXUAL ENERGY OF THE GROUP LIKE? The sexual energy level varies depending on who shows up and is often higher at private homes but the focus is always on the art. This is not a hook-up event.

WHAT IF I GET AN ERECTION? Erections are natural and are welcome. However, when you're socializing or supposed to be drawing, masturbating is not okay.

WHO KEEPS THE DRAWINGS THAT I POSED FOR? Each artist keeps his own drawings. The model can ask for/trade/buy other artists' drawings.

Organized by Shungaboy

Our social media:

Our Website: http://mndgny.com...

Our Twitter: https://twitter.com/M...

Our Facebook Page: https://www.facebook....

Our Wordpress Blog: http://mndgny.wordpre...

Updated 1/20/2016

results.description:
When the schedule says a start time it doesn't mean you have to be there at the specified start time. you can arrange to come at any point from start time to 8 pm. Saturday & Sunday activities are available all day long not just starting at 9 am. Just say you will be attending for the day and tell me what time you plan to show up than watch for my confirmation reply. If you have my text # already you can contact me via text as well but please if you can also show attendance on this site if you can't I totally understand it can get tedious signing in at this site for every class. I've experienced it myself attending other people's meetups. I'm Rob by name. Adrenalhigh Rob or Sergeant Pain if you prefer. :-) Now for the information about this training.

This group will include outdoor martial arts training and outdoor social sports in NYC & BK as well as indoor martial arts training on rainy and cold days in Brooklyn.

All training and sports will be on a first request basis. Whomever requests whichever activity on any given day / time is what we will do.

Tennis & Paddle Ball 

For tennis I will bring 100 balls and we will do drills first than play a game than review our weaknesses and drill our weaknesses. There will be no charge for this unless you need to borrow a racquet than it will be a $5 charge for racquet rental.

Social & Competitive Volleyball & Badminton:
Coming soon

Martial Arts:

Though martial arts classes show starting at a specific time you can arrive at any time from the start time to as late as 8 pm. Just let me know what time you plan to arrive. However, it's always preferred you come at the beginning of a session.

I've been doing Martial Arts since very young and am over 40 now. We will cover the following.

Wing Chun

Muay Thai

BJJ-Brazilian Jiu Jitsu

Hung Ga

Choy Lay Fut

Philippine Stick Fighting

Traditional European Fencing-Not Olympic style but the style used to actually fight / defend yourself.

Chinese Broad Sword

Japanese Sword

Traditional European Fencing

Pole

Spear

Chain Whip

Chi Gung

Tai Chi

Heavy Weapons from SCA / Rennaissance.

This is no joke. I've been doing all of these and more for at least 4 years each up to 20 years for some. Each class will be only $5 for up to 4 hours of training a day. For training in NYC you'll need to bring your own gear if you come to Brooklyn you can use my gear. Please bring the exact amount I won't always have change.

Why am I doing this?

Just to keep my skills sharp. So come and get it if you like a challenge and becoming fit and skilled. Some training will be outdoors on favorable weather days . Otherwise I have a heated garage we will use. I have every weapon you can possibly imagine we'll be using, A Muk Jong / Wooden man and full body protection for at least two people so starting out. As well as kettle bells, lat pull down system, flexibility training devices, elastic bands & iron body conditioning systems. For the colder times of the year come dressed for chilly but not cold temperature and on day 1 you'll see what you will need or may want to get in the future. 

What we train in for the day will be based on who makes the initial training request and a majority preference. 

Don't worry I've done this before and it works out well. 

Before your first class please send me a direct email that you want to attend and what time and where.  For the winter all training will be in Brooklyn, Bensonhurst, D Train to 18th Ave. In the summer trainings will occur either in BK or NYC based on individual request.

On day 1 we'll have to arrange the meeting time so I can come get you. After day 1 you'll be able to come at any point. 

NOTE WHEN I DID THIS BEFORE THERE ARE ALWAYS PEOPLE WHO SAY THEY ARE COMING BUT DON"T SHOW UP. NO SHOWS WITHOUT NOTIFICATION WILL NOT BE ABLE TO CONTINUE. I OFFER A THREE STRIKE POLICY

The mission of New Jersey Screenwriters is to provide formal tools to established and aspiring screenwriters alike while also fostering a sense of community and mutual learning that engenders friendship, fellowship and the potential to create marketable products. Peer to peer feedback will be a routine aspect of each meeting along with career guidance from industry professionals. Affording opportunities to network both personally and professionally is a foundation of this organization. This is accomplished through the following types of monthly events: - Writing Workshops: We bring in industry professionals for hands-on sessions where you can learn new techniques and skills to improve your work. - Feedback Opportunities and Pitching Practice: You will have many opportunities to present in front of your peers in order to gain exposure and gather feedback. - Networking Events: Meet other writers, actors, directors, producers, and other industry professionals to explore and form new collaborations. - Film Screenings: We curate films based on the group's interest to stimulate and facilitate group discussion and learning. - Guest Speaker Series: We invite active industry professionals who will share their experiences, insights, and advice. The programming of this group and the nature of the support will grow and align with the needs of New Jersey Screenwriters (NJS) members.

Welcome to the NYC chapter of Enough4All! We're a group of creative people who care about changing the world for the better. We host events that highlight the intersection of the arts/media/creativity and social transformation, including live interviews and happy hour mixers. results.description:
CCNYC is the local chapter of Conscious Capitalism, a national organization rooted in the principles of Conscious Capitalism as described by John Mackey and Raj Sisodia in their seminal book.

The commitment to create a Conscious Capitalism Chapter in one of the world’s global financial centers presents a unique opportunity. Those of us spearheading the effort have felt a great sense of responsibility to create an organization that not only reflects the character and commerce of this city, but also supports the tenets of Conscious Capitalism in a place that unquestionably has tremendous influence over the way capitalism is practiced in the world today. As we move forward, we want to acknowledge the special circumstances and enormous opportunities inherent in building a chapter so close to Wall Street. And so, we’ve come to the conclusion as a group that our chapter must be as inclusive as this city, and also as driven.

We believe Conscious Capitalism is a new paradigm for operating corporations; one that recognizes the power of capitalism to improve the human condition and create enduring value for all stakeholders. We invite anyone who is curious about these ideas and those who already embrace them to join us as we reach high and strive to create change in our society.

“A mystical approach to Judaism is…less dogmatic and more experimental. It doesn’t have a low ceiling, capping the mind and frustrating its desire to unify in love and awe with a vital, living universe. It is open minded, open souled. It says, ‘Try this. If you feel it as a living reality, we’re getting somewhere.’” 

Reb Zalman Schachter-Shalomi zt”l 

This is an incredibly exciting time to be Jewish! As the paradigms shift, it is becoming increasingly clear that much of Judaism is rapidly evolving into a community more attuned to the inner life and focused on awakening, that is, the expansion of consciousness. 

Uri! Uri! Awaken! Awaken! A Community of Spiritual Seekers (for Jews and Non-Jews), now emerging in Flatbush (Brooklyn), is a part of this exciting transition, and we invite you into our experimental boat!

results.description:
Life in New York is fun but it does take a toll on us. We are always in a rush, always in transition. By the weekend or a day off, we are exhausted and don't even feel that accomplished. In all this vanity, we hardly spend any time with our friends, people we could open ours souls to. We almost never have time or possibility to sit down with a trusted friend and open up about our thoughts and feelings. We push it all down in a constant chase for New York life. No wonder, we get burned out, we loose touch with who we are. Then we make mistakes in our choices when it comes to careers and relationships. We get lost. 
So my dear Goddess we need to find time to create that safe place where we could come together, release our concerns and worries, open our hearts and souls, and connect with our femininity. Let's find the power in sisterhood, and empower each other by connecting and sharing our minds, hearts and souls. Let's create judgment free space to harbor our femininity and empower each other to live in this crazy and amazing city.

Are you ready for an organization that's only for business owners and is focused on helping you work "ON" your business rather than just "IN" your business? Created by bestselling author, speaker and entrepreneur, Tim Houston, Level Up members are small business owners and entrepreneurs from a variety of different industries and ofline professions -- both online and offline -- who appreciate the ability to share ideas, solve problems and identify opportunities for one another, all with the goals of becoming more productive, profitable and prosperous!

We are a membership-based organization. At each session, we have a world-class workshop focusing on business development and a time for each of the members to share the challenges & successes they are having in their own businesses.

Our intention is to bring together people at the nexus of consciousness-raising, social entrepreneurship and social change to network and to spotlight individuals, projects, movements, NGO's, and for-good companies that are extending love and creativity into the world in ways that inspire others to do the same. 

We will attempt to bring a spiritual perspective to themes such as environmentalism, sustainability, human rights, economic justice and women's empowerment. From the point of view of spirit, "nothing real can be threatened" [A Course in Miracles]. From this perspective, it is madness to try to change anyone or anything; however, this conclusion hardly precludes action! Once freed from the need to change ourselves or others, we can devote all our thoughts to sharing our love and creativity, and there are an infinite variety of ways we can be kind and helpful to one another. In fact, it is only through sharing our inner creativity and unconditional love that we remember and realize our limitlessness.

To this end we envision hosting documentary film screenings, mixers, lectures, fundraisers, panel discussions, Q&As, and, perhaps later, organizing and/or participating in various social good projects. We value diversity and inclusivity  and invite you to share your voice with the community.

► Big Group Singles Sunset Walk on the High Line

Thank you,
Beau, your Date Walking Organizer
 
Call/Text: 347-225-3516
Email: datewalking@gmail.com

Date Walking | Facebook | Twitter 


I've tried Plenty of Fish, OKcupid, Coffee meets Bagel, Craigslist, Tinder and so on and it's the same thing every time: a little bit of back-and-forth communication that eventually diminishes to nothing. Either that or you actually meet a person here and a person there and there's no chemistry so it's over. More wasted time. I've been hosting walking events on Meetup groups for over 3 years and as far as I'm concerned, it's the best way to meet a woman because you're not just meeting 1 woman. With Date Walking you know.

All evenings are by donation with a suggested donation of $20 per person. We also host special evenings with lightworkers and healers. We are here to create a conscious, sacred and supportive community in the heart of one of the greatest cities in the world. Breathe on with love!

Rebirthing Breathwork, also commonly referred to as rebirthing or conscious connected breathing, is an acceleration of the healing process through an exploration and practice of the breath. Bypassing the mind entirely, the rebirthing breath goes deep into your cells, saturating the body with both oxygen and life force, and helps to release any negative self-thought, perceived limitations, past trauma or any uncomfortable feelings that are held in the body. It is a truly transformational modality that helps the breather recognize their union with their higher self and all of life with peace and absolute love.

results.description:
Welcome at Ultimate Tango!

Here you find all you need to become a true member of Tango community. We focus on developing in you the truth understanding of what Tango is.

Tango is not just a dance. It’s philosophy, the way of comprehending the world, the way of building relationships, the way to understand yourself.

Here at Ultimate Tango we teach you the tango alphabet, we teach you how to create words, we teach you basic rules, basic steps, basic combinations. We teach you all you need to know about music, connection, lead and follow, types of tangos and more. From there you can launch onto your own journey to discover what Tango means for you. 

We don’t want to limit you with multitude of steps and clatter your memory with combinations you can never remember. Our goal is to give you the true understanding of Tango structure and music, mechanics of the movement, technique and cadence. From there you can start improvising on you own. Find your own style.

We offer carefully structured courses in Tango, Vals and Milonga at 3 different levels – beginner, intermediate, advanced at 3 different locations: New York City NY, West New York NJ and Boston MA. We also offer workshops to address more specialized topics. Private lessons are available for those who wish to progress at their own pace.

DON'T REPEAT MINDLESSLY. LEARN THROUGH UNDERSTANDING.
results.name: Ultimate Tango NYC Meetup

While the focus is here in Bay Ridge, we venture off to venues in other parts of Brooklyn, like the Brooklyn Museum and the Heights Players. Membership is NOT limited to only those living in Bay Ridge or even Brooklyn, so those "out on the island" or in one of the other boroughs are welcome, too!

Similar to most meetups, "The (Mostly) Bay Ridge Neighbors" has a modest $1 organizing fee per event, payable to me at the start of an event, to offset the subscription cost of maintaining the meetup.

Please note our No-Show Policy: Because we've been kept waiting in lobbies, etc., for folks who didn't bother to change their rsvps, "The (Mostly) Bay Ridge Neighbors"  has a "no-show" policy where any member who incurs ONE no-show with no explanatory emails to me will be permanently removed from our membership rolls and not be allowed to rsvp for any more of our events. After all, would you keep a "friend" who stood you up and never apologized? Let's all respect each other's time and enjoy ourselves with a minimum of discomfort.

Like what you see about "The (Mostly) Bay Ridge Neighbors "? Then consider joining our sister groups, "Great Places in Gotham" (http://www.meetup.com/The-Great-Places-in-Gotham-Meetup/) , which focuses primarily on Manhattan events and museums, and "Friendly Native New Yorker Walking Tours" (http://www.meetup.com/Friendly-Native-New-Yorker-Walking-Tours/), where as a licensed NYC tour guide, I lead various walking tours in Brooklyn, Manhattan, and Queens!

results.description:
This is not a sit around group, this is trial by fire. If you want to get involved in video production, and are an adult of sound mind and body this may be for you. We meet to voluntarily exchange media and production work.

The rules:

RULE #1: You are not a participant, you are a reporter of the news, you do not place your self in danger, you do not place others in danger, you do not personally comment on situations or editorialize, you cover others at the event talking. They are the subject, not any of us in the meetup.

RULE #2: If you want to make sure what you want get's published, either publish it your self on social media, or, convince someone in the group or outside of the group to publish. Just because you are part of the group, does not mean anyone has any obligation to contribute to your work. This is a loosely based meetup.

RULE #3: Bring your skills. If you like being a reporter, if you want to do audio engineering, if you want to write music with true current social meaning, then this is an opportunity.

RULE #4: Try to share your skills with others, there will always be video to produce, if you want to do video production, audio production, anything in the stream to create a news worthy news piece, this is your opportunity.

RULE #5: Do this because you enjoy it, try to have fun, help others, try make meaning of the chaos.

RULE #6: We attend public meeting using Open Meeting Law, in New Jersey this means you can only video speakers or officials, due to NJ draconian laws the public in a meeting has a 'right to privacy' at a meeting. In New York all present at meeting may be recorded.  Recording can not interfere with an orderly meeting. NOTE: Every meeting will generate media to produce, I will generate it and provide it under Creative Commons, so if you are downstream of Video and Audio capture, don't worry, you will always have at least my work to work with.

I started this group when I found out that out of a city of 6+ million, there was no planned coverage of THE Post Ambrose LNG public hearing in Queens. It does not matter if you are a Conservative, Liberal, Progressive or any other affiliation. If you want to get involved with video production, this is an opportunity. For my personal work, I always publish creative commons, unless I included copy write material granted to me specifically for my production. Musicians and Sound engineers are badly needed.

FYI

BE PREPARED! 

Federal and State hearings for unpopular infrastructure projects happen many times in the dead of winter, on the coldest evening with virtually no public transit access.  When I was at the Queens meeting it was dark and in the teens,  I could not imagine any elderly person or sane person taking a multi-link trip to that location, and saw none waiting at bus stop.

If you want to be on the short list of people to be notified of short notice events, contact me.  I always announce on the website, but sometimes less than 24 hours are given in advance notice.

results.description:
Food and Drink Adventures is geared towards thirty-somethings who want to explore the culinary and nightlife playground that is New York. More than just a drinking and dining-out group, this group is about learning and experiencing all that we consume--as it relates to culture, heritage, history and so much more! 

A few things to note: 

1) Events: All events will be designed to foster friendship.  Dinners will not have large attendance lists, whereas happy hours will not be capped.  

2) Age: This group is intended for people in their 30's.  I'd appreciate it if you respect that. 

3) In an effort to stem the amount of people who RSVP and fail to show up, I’m going to implement the following policy for any person who RSVPs for the 1st time to an event that has a set reservation number and has not shown up to any past events:

When you RSVP as a 1st Timer, I will send you a message to confirm that you will be attending the event. To confirm, simply respond to my message within 48 hours, and you’ll remain on the RSVP list. In the event I do not hear back from you within those 48 hours, if there’s a wait-list, I will remove you from the RSVP list to have someone from the wait-list take your spot.

So please be sure you have your meetup settings allowing me as organizer to send you messages through meetup directly.

4) Removal: If you’re been a member of the group for six months and haven’t RSVP’d or attended a single event, then I reserve the right to remove you from the group. I know that there are a ton of meetup options for one to partake in this great city, but I hope that if you signed up for this group, you’re genuinely interested in giving it a shot – stop by for a drink at one the the next happy hours, or take a chance and try a new cuisine while meeting some new folks. 

Also, if you've RSVP'd to at least 2 meetups, and fail to show up without changing your RSVP and/or notifying me of your absence, I reserve the right to remove you from the group. C'mon, guys - it takes 2 seconds to change your RSVP and/or notify me - I don't have the patience for flaky people - feel free to join another group that will tolerate such behavior.

5) Fees: I think it's lame that meetup has fees to begin with and hasn't figured out a way to generate revenue without holding Head Organizers liable for such costs, but it is what it is...with that being said, I'm not sure if there will be a nominal fee for meetups at some later point in time - as I just took over for the previous organizer, I'm still trying to figure this out.

If all this sounds good to you, then join us! :)

results.description:
This is a group for girls who live in Greenpoint and Williamsburg. Meetups will include a little bit of everything - dinners, happy hours, fitness activities, shopping, galleries, coffee, festivals, and more! Girls in this group should be in their 20s and 30s only, no exceptions. Most events will have attendance limits, because it's easier to get to know each other in a smaller group! However, don't be discouraged by the waitlist - people tend to cancel in the days right before the event, so you definitely can make it into the events from the waitlist! Inactive members are subject to removal, so please try to make it to some of the events! **I will frequently remove all members who have not even looked at the group page in over a month.** This group will remain small, so we're all able to get to know each other!

*Attendance Policy:

*Respect and consideration for others are Top Priority; be considerate by refraining from being a "NO SHOW" (Not showing up and leaving your RSVP a "yes", or changing RSVP to a "no" within 2 hours of an event and not communicating with the organizer) or a "LATE CANCEL" (Cancelling out of an event within 24 hrs of the event).

*Events take work for organizers to coordinate, especially those requiring RSVPs. Make sure you are able to make it to an event to which you RSVP and if you anticipate a conflict or being late, give us a heads up. We understand that things come up and life interferes, but please do your best. ;)

*If you find that you can't make it to something you've signed up for -- CHANGE YOUR RSVP as soon as possible, or call/text/message an organizer/event host if it is within 2 hours of the event. Events take time & energy to plan. If you don't show up AND make no effort to let the Event Planner know what happened --- that's a "NO SHOW".

*No Show/Late Cancel policy: If you have a history of doing this (we keep track of attendance on your profile), we won't be able to count on you to show up when you say you are going to. Out of respect and courtesy to others that DO show up, we may bump you to the waiting list for meetups with limited space in favor of those with a positive attendance history. If you make a habit out of no showing or late cancelling, we may remove you from the group.

results.description: We all have knowledge and talents to share- so let's get together and teach and learn from each other! This is an opportunity to build a community through a "smorgasbord of knowledge" that we constantly create. The idea is simple: Every two weeks we will meet to experience something led by one of the members of the group. We will each have an opportunity to sign up to teach a topic, lead a workshop, give a lecture or anything in between for up to 45 minutes. This is a chance to try new things and have different experiences that we hope, in turn, will build community. As members of this group we have one goal: to help grow our community of knowledge by sharing of ourselves and of course, have fun in the process! That means simply participating or signing up to lead us in a presentation. Is there anything you've always wanted to try but never did or a way you've wanted to push yourself, or something you love deeply that you wish you did more? Anything can be the theme of your presentation to the group- from a juggling workshop to a lecture on evolution to a story of your travels to origami- what matters is that you bring something to the group that you love and are excited to share. On your assigned presentation week please be sure to come prepared with any materials you might need and of course let the group know if anything should be done in advance. Then  the rest of us will learn, grow, and be enriched....until it's our turn to present and enrich others! And don't forget everyone bring your favorite wine or beer to share with the group for some mingling after the presentation!
results.name: Brooklyn Knowledge Smorgasbord

topics.name: The Impact of Lyme on your Life

results.description:
" But you look so good?"  Sound familiar?  Lyme disease is one of the "invisible diseases" and often lyme patients suffer consequences of "not looking sick" - jobs are lost, family and friends don't understand, doctors don't believe you or want to treat you, etc., etc. In addition, Lyme Patients often, due to crushing fatigue and pain, find themselves alone and isolated unable to go to work or socialize, which can negatively impact one's ability to recover.

This group is Open to Lyme Disease Patients and Friends and Family of Lyme Patients for the purpose of establishing a community of support and creating a safe venue for sharing experiences, challenges, information and camaraderie.  Located on the Upper West Side of Manhattan, the meetings are facilitated by an acupuncturist, sound healer and experienced meditator, who is also diagnosed with neurological lyme. Sessions will include guided-meditation, group discussion and possibly sound/music therapy.
results.name: NYC Lyme Disease Support Group

results.description:
This is a group consisting of individuals interested in discovering how to walk through various NYC streets and look for how to "read" the streets for interesting architectural and historic facts. As a licensed NYC Tour Guide, I will show you how to detect a specific historic block, and then we'll  determine the reason that block is "historic". We'll them move onto other sites where I'll share some stories you in turn can share with your friends(who aren't lucky enough to have joined the group).

I started this group as I wanted to share my knowledge with New Yorkers(native or new) during my slow winter season when I'm not as busy with foreigners and student groups. Since one  of my hobbies is photography, we'll definitely stop by some spots where you can take "bug eye" or "bird's eye" photos and truly realize how those descriptors came about…In fact, as we walk, you may end up suggesting and sharing with the group a better photo ops that the ones I have planned!

 My goal is for all of us to have fun and take away  lasting memories from our time together exploring New York. An extra  bonus would be if some of you decide to meet again (either in a group setting or just an informal twosome), but there are no guarantees. HOWEVER, at the end of the walk, I plan on enjoying a  a low cost snack in an  indoor public space. I hope you all decide to join me for our "Apres Walk"(i.e. my version of "Apres Ski" fun). Incidentally,  you can either bring something with you or purchase something along the way. 

I'll also be happy to share with you info on some  other upcoming   low cost/freebie events/venues for the coming week. I hope you can also  share some other FREEBIE events info with our group. For example, after a Friday walk in  midtown Manhattan, I can direct you to 2 midtown museums where on  Fridays 1 is FREE and the other is "pay-as-you-wish" night. 



The $15 charge per person is to help cover administrative costs. You still will be getting a tour very similar to  my $250 private tours.

Thank you for becoming a member and I hope you join some  of our tours soon!

results.description:
This workshop introduces performing techniques that business professionals can start using to master the “soft” skills that many companies are seeking – creativity, communication, teamwork, leadership and strong interpersonal skills.

Objectives
1. Use performing techniques to improve your charisma and presence.
2. Learn to stretch your comfort zone and manage stage fright. Take risks. Think creatively. Think fast on your feet.
3. Discover how to market yourself to colleges or employers. What makes you unique? Gain new awareness of your public persona.

Details
Each workshop is different and may focus on new skills or build upon previous exercises. We provide a supportive environment for beginners.

The workshop may start out with a guided vocal and physical warm up. The awakening of vocal resonators and energizing the body will make you grounded in any job interview or business presentation.

We may do a series of improvisational acting exercises geared towards getting you out of your comfort zone to create characters, stories and conflict within a scene on the spot. This gears you for being quick on your feet and thinking fast in the work place, and also gets people out of their comfort zone as they create these quirky and extroverted characters.

Other exercises will involve using all these acting tools in a business setting.

For meet up members the price is $20 per class. If you would like unlimited monthly classes for $49, please check out https://bookeo.com/academyonbroadway/signup

For more workshops, check out www.academyonbroadway.com

About Theology on Tap: Have you ever noticed that sometimes your best and deepest theological reflections happen outside of your place of worship, when you are hanging out with friends? We have too, and that is the whole idea behind Theology on Tap.  Our Theology on Tap is for those who embrace the questions, rather than those who embrace answers - meaning that if you are hoping to tell everyone your "truth," but are unwilling to listen to the "truth" of others, this isn't for you.  This is for people of all faiths, all denominations within faiths, and those who are seekers.  And, as a result, it has really taken off! Past topics have included “Pluralism: How can we talk about God without killing each other?”, “Faith: What’s that all about?”, and “Why are we here?: An exploration of the meaning of our existence.” The topic in January will be “A New Year, A New Faith?: What questions and challenges do we need to explore in the year ahead, and which spiritual practices are best for you?”

results.description:
This workshop is for those who want to reclaim the power to live your life fully. By learning ancient Toltec techniques to master awareness, shift limiting beliefs, and change your story, you bring YOU back to life and reclaim your authenticity and happiness. 

You will learn how to integrate The 4 agreements (by don Miguel Ruiz) into every day life and learn ancient Toltec tools (recapitulation, mirroring, dreaming, intent) to recreate your dream with integrity and love. In the workshop series, we will do exercises to master each of the 4 agreements (Be Impeccable With Your Word, Don't Take Anything Personally, Don't Make Assumptions, Always Do Your Best), learn healing techniques to release fear at the cell level, and create a community of support and action moving toward creating our new dream with awareness. 

Each workshop will have a topic related to one of the agreements, exercises or games, and open time for support, a closing ceremony and homework to integrate into daily life. It will be fun, uplifting, powerful and supportive group which will meet bi-weekly. You can go to all the classes or pop in to any one, because they will each be complete in their own way and do not progress in a specific order or sequence. All the agreements are addressed over and over again from different aspects, and different exercises, tools etc are shared to help integrate each one into daily life.
results.name: Awaken Through Dreaming Meditation & Healing Exercises!

results.description:
Entrepreneurship is an art form, responsible in part for shaping the state of human affairs. As innovators and members of a global community we should strive to better understand the nature of our thoughts and actions. Why do we defy the odds to pursue our goals? How can we transcend ego, cultivate mindfulness and calibrate our efforts to serve a greater good?

Insight awakens by calming the mind and peering inward; A daunting task for the often extroverted entrepreneur. While it may be difficult or appear as counter-productive, we can expand our awareness of self and thus begin to realize the innate wisdom that has become buried under layers of social conditioning. 

While this process may be confusing or even spiritually disruptive, it is the first step toward rejecting the “me first” mentality in favor of benevolence. Let’s explore such topics in the context of entrepreneurship through community-driven discussions, with an objective to challenge our present beliefs and redefine what it means to be a leader in modern business.
results.name: Philosophy of Social Entrepreneurship

results.description:
Why Join The Blogger Babes Meetup group? 

It can get lonely for anyone trying to blog her way to the top. That’s why we formed The Blogger Babes. It’s not just an  association –  it’s more like a sisterhood. We help each other out, from sharing useful tips  to collaborating with members to create awesome content together.

You’ll benefit from our experienced bloggers - those that have been blogging for quite a while and who actually make a living from their blog - to our handy tips and tools , networking opportunities and the educational webinars we coordinate at least twice a month.

We offer some pretty exciting (and exclusive) stuff:

· Socializing and Networking Opportunities: Hang out with your fellow bloggers, both in person and virtually! We organize parties, meetups and webinars for our Blogger Babes. 

· Exclusive Content: Hone your skills, cultivate new ideas and pick up a few tips with our content – ebooks, articles, webinars and more! Only available to Blogger Babes members.

·Support: The Blogger Babes are a friendly bunch – and we encourage members to reach out to one another, to make friends, collaborate, give encouragement and seek advice from members. You can’t do everything by yourself, and you shouldn’t have to when your fellow blogger babes are such excellent sources of support.

Goodies & Gifts & Sponsored Opportunities: We're continuously working to find sponsors for our bloggers. It's a win-win situation for both parties - our sponsors get exposure and feedback about their products & services, and our bloggers get to try out new products and services for free . This also gives a chance for our newer bloggers to learn how to review products the right way ( yes, there is a right and wrong way to write spectacular product reviews that will keep your sponsors coming back and your readers clamoring for more..).

Does this all sound exciting? Come join us and start blogging better now, and do tell all the other bloggers  in your life to join the Blogger Babes movement.

PS:Make sure you subscribe to our no-cost newsletter at www.bloggerbabes.com to get all of this week’s valuable content in condensed form.

Our mission is to bring adventure and fun into your life while building lifelong friendships. Are you tired of sitting at home? Is it hard to get together with friends who are married or have moved away? Is the weekly bar scene getting boring and old to you? Well you are not alone! results.description:
This Group is for Woman who suffer from Mood Disorders ages 21+ only.

VERY IMPORTANT: We have a limit of 50 members in our group. Once we've reached 50, the remaining women will be placed on a waitlist, and will be on it until a spot opens up. Because of this, we urge our members to participate as much as possible, because if not, your simply taking up a membership spot from those women on the waitlist. 

What we are About: Our group is to reach out to woman in the New York area who suffer from Mood Disorders "diagnosed or not" for support, friendship, understanding, no judgement and inspire happiness. This group will bond woman of ages 21+ who can relate and understand one another through the voices of honest experiences-past and present as well as develop new long term friendships with exciting group activities.

Please visit our facebook page: Www.facebook.com/strongwomenwithmd

Visit our blog page: Strongwomenwithmd.wordpress.com

Visit our Twitter page: Strong Women with MD

Visit our Instagram: STRONG_WOMEN_W_MD

Our Goal:  To help women just like us with mood disorders... Have you ever had a day where you could not get out of bed, a day where you lied to get out of a date that was planned, a night/week you could not sleep, a day where you could not eat or ate too much, a day you could not pay your bills, a day you realized you were the reason for losing your jobs, a day where no one understood you, a day you felt all alone, or even a day where you felt as if you wanted to die? That STOPS NOW!

Our hope for this group is to be there for one another through these times with support and no judgement. Our group is to build bonds with honesty that will lead to communication, trust and hopefully long term friendships that will result in fun activities.

This group will have weekly meet ups for group discussion about ourselves and share stories in a nonjudgemental fun setting or group activity.

Group Commitment: This group will require you to be 100% honest in commitment to yourself and all of us when joining. We will ask you to read, post and share in our blog which will help inspire yourself and others. This blog will be about us, gratification and our success in friendship.  This is a very therapeutic tool for yourself and to inspire others.

strongwomenwithmd.wordpress.com 

RSVP & Attendee Policy: You should be able to attend at least one event per month. Anyone who has not attended an event within the first few months of joining will be removed. as the goal is to be an active member. If you RSVP yes, please do not cancel the day of the event. If you need to cancel, please do so within 48 hours of the event. No shows will not be tolerated and can lead to removal from the group. Changing your RSVP on the day of the event without notification is just as bad as not showing up. We take the time to make reservations and hold spot for you. Please keep the event host informed. 

Please understand and thank you.

Keep in mind we are not licensed doctors or therapists. We are just like you. This group consists of woman sharing their stories and are here to listen and support only.

We look forward to meeting you,

Megan, Vanessa, Jaleesa

A STRONG WOMAN is one who feels deeply and loves fiercely. Her tears flow just as abundantly as her laughter. A STRONG WOMAN is both soft and powerful. She is both practical and spiritual. A STRONG WOMAN in her essence is a GIFT to the world!
results.name: Friendship & Support Group For Women With Mood Disorders

results.description:
Kizomba/Semba Classes & Events by David Campos & Guida Rei in NEW JERSEY AREA

☞ What is Kizomba – The Origin

Kizomba is a breath whose rhythm is a beating heart, and where the perfect connection between two dancers gives birth to harmony, exaltation of senses and sensuality" D. Campos

Kizomba (a word meaning "Party" in angola ) takes its origin from the Angolan dance Semba, which is also the origin of the Brazilian Samba.

It appeared at the end of 70’s – 80’s, while the young Angolans, although very attached to their traditional dance,sought a new musical identity, and finally found their inspiration and new voice at a concert given by Kassav, a famous French Caribbean Zouk band. Kizomba was born out of this new generation’s desire to bring a touch of sensuality and sweetness to their national Semba.

The influence of the Angolan Kizomba soon spread to all the African Lusophone countries such as Guinea Bisau, Cape Verde, Mozambique. From there the dance quickly found its ticket to Europe via Portugal, where it further developed, by all these Artists, teachers, choregraphers coming from
these Luso-African countries.

As it rapidly gained popularity, Portugal exported Kizomba to various countries in Europe such as France, Spain, Poland, Belgium, Danemark and England. Today it is rare to find a Latin dance party without Kizomba represented, as well as salsa or bachata.

This "African Tango Zouk", also called "Tango Lusophone" continues to conquer a growing audience of passionate dancers, eager for beauty of gesture and sensuality, but also the indispensable complexity of exchange and trust present in each motions of Kizomba.

This young dance of barely thirty years is booming today, and constantly evolving.

"Kizomba is a tribute to sensuality, an ode to love and sharing. A moment when the woman's beauty, enhanced by her partner, must embody all its essence. " D. Campos

Be the pioneers here in the U.S. of a dance that will become soon a must for your dancing nightlife !!!
results.name: kizomba/semba in New Jersey
